dct_title_s: The Literary Digest liberty map of the Western Front of the Great World War showing the battle line of liberty as it stood September 5th, 1918
dct_description_sm: engraved and printed by the Matthews-Northrup Works, Buffalo, N.Y.

Insets: Map of the complete war area showing Russian, Italian, Balkan, Palestine and Mesopotamian campaigns; also the zones of submarine blockade -- The coal and iron fields in the western war territory -- Production of pig iron in metric tons [and] coal in short tons.
